ull_resolution": []}, "title": "In a blow to Democrats, two Republican candidates in California's 40th Congressional District have advanced to the General election.  ", "last_comment_created": 1780862941247, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 4, "score_up": 26, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "Two Republican candidates in California's 40th Congressional District have advanced to the general election in a blow to Democrats.", "large_image": "BSSfTQJxwOQY4u6O.png", "title": "CA's 40th Congressional District to Feature Republican Versus Republican"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsnFaHyr", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 31, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8665571, "raw_content": "Mormons have been very fair & generous in their dealings with me-- so I was resistant when I read the phrase 'Mormon Mafia'  being tossed-around loosely in Comments-- on PDW & YouTube.\n\nBUT:\n\n1. a YouTube channel hosted by ex-communicated Mormons-- reported an old newspaper article & local tv news video-- showing that Bricks&Minifigs CEO Ammon...  and Josh (the guy who took-over ownership of the store from the woman who gave the consignment deal)... were paired as TEENAGE mormon MISSIONARIES in New Orleans, years ago.     I haven't seen Anyone Else except the ex-mormons reveal that connection.\n\n2. the unredacted bodycam footage which the American Forks Utah Police accidentally leaked (by placing it in the PD's public DropBox/ where it was found by 'hackers')...    included a moment where Josh was on his doorstep/ telling the cops \"I'm on the High Council\".    Which is a prestigious position held by only 12 of the \"most qualified, most honorable men in the community.\" Josh's title would literally be \"High Priest\", overseeing between 5 & 12 churches.        AFTER that leaked-- the Latter-Day Saints announced Josh has been removed from the High Council.\n\n3. In the leaked footage-- Josh also tells the cops that CEO Ammon had reached-out to Josh with an offer:   If Josh would go supervise kicking the original owner Chrystal out of the store-- Josh's payment would be that Josh could \"keep whatever inventory\" Josh \"recovered\".       \n\nSo... Josh had incentive to get greedy & try to take the consigned Star Wars stuff for himself.    And then his ol' missionary buddy CEO Ammon backed-up Josh's greedy-grab.  \n\nWhich was detrimental to the other 200+ Bricks&Minifigs store Franchise owners--   who are bearing the brunt of public backlash.     \n\nCEO Ammon put his personal connection to Josh ahead of his CEO obligations to the 200+ Franchise Owners.\n\nThe American Forks PD put their ties to CEO Ammon & Josh-- ahead of their sworn duty to provide equal justice for all.\n\n- -\n\nThe B.A.M. (Bricks & Minifigs corporate) press release-- announcing that the corporation had \"parted ways\" [fired] Josh... ~may~ genuinely be B.A.M.  Throwing-Josh-Under-The-Bus.         \n\nOr that may be a bogus Public Relations ploy-- with CEO Ammon & Josh still closely coordinating, behind the scenes.\n\nWhich also applies to Josh's franchise co-owner (and Josh's mormon neighbor in Utah) Brandon Best... who was also named in the \"parting ways\" press release.", "author": "Lunar", "created": 1780855295176, "profile_picture": "AAVSlrgdPsSU", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "2016TrumpMAGA", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "I was initially wary of \"Mormon Mafia\" accusations.  But the accusations DO have substance.  (If you didn't go down the Bricks&Minifigs/ Reckless Ben/ Star Wars Lego rabbit hole... this post is not for you.   If you did... this post may \"crack the case\"!)", "last_comment_created": 1780865801138, "content": "<p>Mormons have been very fair &amp; generous in their dealings with me-- so I was resistant when I read the phrase 'Mormon Mafia'  being tossed-around loosely in Comments-- on PDW &amp; YouTube.</p>\n<p>BUT:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>a YouTube channel hosted by ex-communicated Mormons-- reported an old newspaper article &amp; local tv news video-- showing that Bricks&amp;Minifigs CEO Ammon...  and Josh (the guy who took-over ownership of the store from the woman who gave the consignment deal)... were paired as TEENAGE mormon MISSIONARIES in New Orleans, years ago.     I haven't seen Anyone Else except the ex-mormons reveal that connection.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>the unredacted bodycam footage which the American Forks Utah Police accidentally leaked (by placing it in the PD's public DropBox/ where it was found by 'hackers')...    included a moment where Josh was on his doorstep/ telling the cops &quot;I'm on the High Council&quot;.    Which is a prestigious position held by only 12 of the &quot;most qualified, most honorable men in the community.&quot; Josh's title would literally be &quot;High Priest&quot;, overseeing between 5 &amp; 12 churches.        AFTER that leaked-- the Latter-Day Saints announced Josh has been removed from the High Council.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>In the leaked footage-- Josh also tells the cops that CEO Ammon had reached-out to Josh with an offer:   If Josh would go supervise kicking the original owner Chrystal out of the store-- Josh's payment would be that Josh could &quot;keep whatever inventory&quot; Josh &quot;recovered&quot;.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>So... Josh had incentive to get greedy &amp; try to take the consigned Star Wars stuff for himself.    And then his ol' missionary buddy CEO Ammon backed-up Josh's greedy-grab.</p>\n<p>Which was detrimental to the other 200+ Bricks&amp;Minifigs store Franchise owners--   who are bearing the brunt of public backlash.</p>\n<p>CEO Ammon put his personal connection to Josh ahead of his CEO obligations to the 200+ Franchise Owners.</p>\n<p>The American Forks PD put their ties to CEO Ammon &amp; Josh-- ahead of their sworn duty to provide equal justice for all.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<ul>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The B.A.M. (Bricks &amp; Minifigs corporate) press release-- announcing that the corporation had &quot;parted ways&quot; [fired] Josh... ~may~ genuinely be B.A.M.  Throwing-Josh-Under-The-Bus.</p>\n<p>Or that may be a bogus Public Relations ploy-- with CEO Ammon &amp; Josh still closely coordinating, behind the scenes.</p>\n<p>Which also applies to Josh's franchise co-owner (and Josh's mormon neighbor in Utah) Brandon Best... who was also named in the &quot;parting ways&quot; press release.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 12, "score_up": 31, "is_edited": true, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}], "status": true}